r 8, 2013}}</ref>\n|elevation_m            = 716\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              = \n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|blank1_name            =\n|blank1_info            =\n|website                =\n|footnotes              = \n}} <!--Infobox ends-->\n\n'''Acadia Valley''' is a [[hamlet (place)|hamlet]] in southeast [[Alberta]] within the [[Municipal District of Acadia No. 34|Municipal District (M.D.) of Acadia No. 34]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://municipalaffairs.gov.ab.ca/documents/msb/2010-ruralmun.pdf |title=Specialized and Rural Municipalities and Their Communities |author=Alberta Municipal Affairs |authorlink=Alberta Municipal Affairs |date=2010-04-01 |accessdate=2010-06-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229060335/http://municipalaffairs.gov.ab.ca/documents/msb/2010-ruralmun.pdf |archivedate=2012-02-29 }}</ref> The M.D. of Acadia No. 34's [[List of municipal districts in Alberta#Office locations|municipal office]] is located in Acadia Valley.\n\nAcadia Valley is located along [[Alberta Highway 41|Highway 41]] commonly referred to as Buffalo Trail between [[Oyen, Alberta|Oyen]] and [[Medicine Hat, Alberta|Medicine Hat]] and sits about {{convert|14.5|km|mi|abbr=on}} west of the Alberta-Saskatchewan border. Acadia Valley sits at a elevation of {{convert|716|m|ft|abbr=on}}.\n\nThe hamlet is located within [[census division]] [[Division No. 4, Alberta|No. 4]].\n\n== Demographics ==\nAs a designated place in the [[Canada 2016 Census|2016 Census of Population]] conducted by [[Statistics Canada]], Acadia Valley recorded a population of 149 living in 71 of its 82 total private dwellings, a change of {{percentage|{{#expr:149-137}}|137|1}} from its 2011 population of 137. With a land area of {{convert|0.47|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}, it had a population density of {{Pop density|149|0.47|km2|sqmi|prec=1}} in 2016.<ref name=2016censusABdpls>{{cite web | url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/hlt-fst/pd-pl/Table.cfm?Lang=Eng&T=1301&SR=1&S=45&O=A&RPP=9999&PR=48&CMA=0#tPopDwell | title=Population and dwelling counts, for Canada, provinces and territories, and designated places, 2016 and 2011 censuses \u2013 100% data (Alberta) | publisher=[[Statistics Canada]] | date=February 8, 2017 | accessdate=February 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAs a designated place in the [[Canada 2011 Census|2011 Census]], Acadia Valley had a population of 137 living in 59 of its 63 total dwellings, a -2.1% change from its 2006 population of 140. With a land area of {{convert|0.48|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}, it had a population density of {{Pop density|137|0.48|km2|sqmi}} in 2011.<ref name=statcan2011dpl>{{cite web | url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2011/dp-pd/hlt-fst/pd-pl/Table-Tableau.cfm?LANG=Eng&T=1302&PR=48&S=51&O=A&RPP=25 | title=Population and dwelling counts, for Canada, provinces and territories, and designated places, 2011 and 2006 censuses (Alberta) | publisher=Statistics Canada | date=2012-02-08 | accessdate=2012-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== Attractions ==\n* [[Prairie Elevator Museum]]<ref>[http://www.mdacadia.ab.ca/mdacadia/interest.htm M.D. of Acadia No. 34] - Points of Interest</ref>\n* Acadia Municipal Recreation Dam - [[trout]] fishing\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of communities in Alberta]]\n*[[List of designated places in Alberta]]\n*[[List of hamlets in Alberta]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.mdacadia.ab.ca/mdacadia/av.htm Hamlet of Acadia Valley] from the M.D. of Acadia No. 34 official web site\n*[http://www.prairie-towns.com/acadiavalley-images.html Historical Photos of Acadia Valley (Prairie-Towns.com)]\n\n{{Alberta|hamlets=yes}}\n{{Alberta Regions Red Deer}}\n{{coord|51|09|25|N|110|12|35|W|scale:60000_region:CA|display=title|name=Acadia Valley}}\n\n[[Category:Municipal District of Acadia No. 34]]\n[[Category:Hamlets in Alberta]]\n[[Category:Designated 