{"title_page": "Tucker Albrizzi", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Tucker Albrizzi\n| image =\n| caption = Albrizzi in 2017\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|2000|02|25}}\n| birth_place = [[Palm Harbor, Florida|Palm Harbor]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| height =\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| spouse = \n| domestic_partner = \n| children = \n| parents = Keith Albrizzi (father)<br />Claudine Andrews (mother)\n| website = {{URL|http://www.tucker-albrizzi.com/}}\n}}\n'''Tucker Albrizzi''' (born February 25, 2000) is an American actor. He is best known for his roles as [[List of Big Time Rush characters#Tyler Duncan|Tyler Duncan]] on ''[[Big Time Rush]],'' [[Good Luck Charlie#Recurring characters|Jake]] on ''[[Good Luck Charlie]],'' Randall Snyder on ''American Vandal'' and Colin McConnell on ''[[A.P. Bio]]''.  He has appeared in such movies as ''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]'', ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'', ''[[Sicko]]'', and ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nAlbrizzi was born and raised in [[Palm Harbor, Florida]], the son of Claudine Andrews and Keith Albrizzi, and the brother of Patrick Pedraja and Chef Jocelyn Albrizzi.\n\n==Career==\nHe began acting in commercials in [[Orlando, Florida]] in 2007 when he was 7 years old. His brother Patrick was diagnosed with [[Leukemia]] later that year and created a charity called Driving for Donors, which adds marrow donors to the [[National Marrow Donor Program|Be The Match]] National Marrow Donor Program. Albrizzi and his family spent the next year traveling the country in an RV holding marrow drives for Driving For Donors. He came to [[Los Angeles]] in 2008 to be in a documentary with Patrick about Driving For Donors and decided to try acting in [[Hollywood]]. Albrizzi and his brother appeared together in [[Michael Moore]]'s ''[[Sicko]]'' and as guests on ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]''.\n\nWithin 2 months of arriving in Hollywood, Albrizzi booked his first series regular role in ''Bless This Mess''. In 2009, he was cast in the recurring role of [[List of Big Time Rush characters#Tyler Duncan|Tyler]] on ''[[Big Time Rush]]''. Later that year, he was also cast in the recurring role of [[Good Luck Charlie#Recurring characters|Jake]], Gabe's best friend, on ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' and guest starred on many other TV shows as well.\n\nIn 2010, Albrizzi began acting in movies with appearances in ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'', ''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]'', and ''[[Treasure Buddies]]''. In 2011, he was originally cast in ''[[Ted (film)|Ted]]'' in the role of Robert, but he was unable to film because of scheduling conflicts with his work on the [[Disney XD]] pilot ''Pack of Wolves''. In the same year, he also got a role as the Kite Kid in ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''.\n\nIn 2016, Albrizzi co-starred in the science fiction action film ''[[Monster Trucks (film)|Monster Trucks]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/pitch-perfect-2-casting-chrissie-fit-monster-trucks-tucker-albrizzi-shohreh-aghdashloo/ |title=Chrissie Fit Cast In \u2018Pitch Perfect 2\u2032; Shohreh Aghdashloo To Narrate \u2018Alam High School\u2019; Tucker Albrizzi Joins \u2018Monster Trucks\u2019|accessdate=April 29, 2014|publisher=deadline.com |date=April 24, 2014}}</ref> In 2017, he starred in the feature film, ''Bully'', as the lead character Jimmy Mulligan.  Albrizzi also played the recurring role of Terry in 10 episodes of the YouTube series ''Foursome''. He also appeared as Randall Snyder in the first 4 episodes of the Netflix series ''[[American Vandal]]''.  Albrizzi appears in all 13 episodes of the first season of ''[[A.P. Bio]]'', as Colin McConnell. He plays Walter Dobbs in all 10 episodes of the first season of ''[[Mr. Iglesias]]'' on Netflix. \n\n===Voiceover work===\nAlbrizzi began [[voice acting]] with 2012's ''[[ParaNorman]]'', in the role of Neil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/livefrom/post/2011/07/paranorman-brings-together-an-outcast-kid-zombies-and-john-hughes/1|title='ParaNorman' brings together an outcast kid, zombies and John Hughes|work=usatoday.com|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref> He was also the voice of Budderball in ''[[Treasure Buddies]]'' (replacing [[Josh Flitter]] from the first ''[[Air Buddies]]'') and played the live-action role of Budderball's owner Bartleby in the [[Air Bud (series)|movies]].{{citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role \n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes \n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Sicko]]''\n|Himself\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''\n|Kite Kid\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]''\n|Skating Kid\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Spooky Buddies]]''\n|Bartleby\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]''\n|Tuck\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Treasure Buddies]]''\n|Budderball\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[ParaNorman]]''\n|Neil (voice)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Monster Trucks (film)|Monster Trucks]]''\n|Sam Geldon\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Bully''\n|Jimmy Mulligan\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[A.P. Bio]]'' (2018) Colin\n* ''[[American Vandal]]'' (2017) Randall Snyder\n* ''Shmagreggie Saves the World'' (2012) Lead role of Shmagreggie (pilot)\n* ''[[Lab Rats (US TV series)|Lab Rats]]'' (2012) Gordo (1 episode)\n* ''[[Disney XD]]'s Pack of Wolves'' (2011) Lead role of Darwin Oppenheimer\n* ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' (2010\u20132014) role of Jake (6 episodes)\n* ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (2009\u20132011) role of Tyler\n* ''[[Zeke and Luther]]'' (2011) role of Fish Belly (2 episodes)\n* ''[[Brothers & Sisters (2006 TV series)|Brothers & Sisters]]'' (2010) role of Kid playing Tybalt\n* ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'' (2010) role of Ricky\n* ''[[Mike & Molly]]'' (2010) role of Tucker\n* ''[[Childrens Hospital]]'' (2010) role of Kid\n* ''[[Dark Blue (TV series)|Dark Blue]]'' (2010) role of Marky\n* ''[[Tim and Eric Awesome Show, Great Job!]]'' (2010) role of iJammer\n* ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'' (2009) role of Son\n* ''[[The Jay Leno Show]]'' (2009) role of Flunker\n* ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]'' (2009) role of The Critics\n* ''Bless This Mess'' (2009) role of Michael\n* ''[[Mr. Iglesias]]'' (2019) role of Walter\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* [[32nd Young Artist Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html|title=32nd Annual Young Artist Awards \u2013 Nominations / Special Awards|work=youngartistawards.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>\n** Best Guest Star Performance in a TV Series \u2013 ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' (Won)\n** Best Recurring Performance in a TV Series \u2013 ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (Nominated)\n* [[33rd Young Artist Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms33.html|title=33rd Annual Young Artist Awards \u2013 Nominations / Special Awards|work=youngartistawards.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>\n** Best Performance in a TV Series \u2013 Guest Starring Young Actor Ten and Under \u2013 ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (Nominated)\n** Best Performance in a DVD Film \u2013 Young Ensemble Cast \u2013 ''[[Spooky Buddies]]'' (Won)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tuckeralbrizzi.com/ Official website]\n* {{IMDb name|3235380}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Albrizzi, Tucker}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:People from Palm Harbor, Florida]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Florida]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Tucker Albrizzi\n| image =\n| caption = Albrizzi in 2017\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|2000|02|25}}\n| birth_place = [[Palm Harbor, Florida|Palm Harbor]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| height =\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| spouse = \n| domestic_partner = \n| children = \n| parents = Keith Albrizzi (father)<br />Claudine Andrews (mother)\n| website = {{URL|http://www.tucker-albrizzi.com/}}\n}}\n'''Tucker Albrizzi''' (born February 25, 2000) is an American actor. He is best known for his roles as [[List of Big Time Rush characters#Tyler Duncan|Tyler Duncan]] on ''[[Big Time Rush]],'' [[Good Luck Charlie#Recurring characters|Jake]] on ''[[Good Luck Charlie]],'' Randall Snyder on ''American Vandal'' and Colin McConnell on ''[[A.P. Bio]]''.  He has appeared in such movies as ''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]'', ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'', ''[[Sicko]]'', and ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nAlbrizzi was born and raised in [[Palm Harbor, Florida]], the son of Claudine Andrews and Keith Albrizzi, and the brother of Patrick Pedraja and Chef Jocelyn Albrizzi.\n\n==Career==\nHe began acting in commercials in [[Orlando, Florida]] in 2007 when he was 7 years old. His brother Patrick was diagnosed with [[Leukemia]] later that year and created a charity called Driving for Donors, which adds marrow donors to the [[National Marrow Donor Program|Be The Match]] National Marrow Donor Program. Albrizzi and his family spent the next year traveling the country in an RV holding marrow drives for Driving For Donors. He came to [[Los Angeles]] in 2008 to be in a documentary with Patrick about Driving For Donors and decided to try acting in [[Hollywood]]. Albrizzi and his brother appeared together in [[Michael Moore]]'s ''[[Sicko]]'' and as guests on ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]''.\n\nWithin 2 months of arriving in Hollywood, Albrizzi booked his first series regular role in ''Bless This Mess''. In 2009, he was cast in the recurring role of [[List of Big Time Rush characters#Tyler Duncan|Tyler]] on ''[[Big Time Rush]]''. Later that year, he was also cast in the recurring role of [[Good Luck Charlie#Recurring characters|Jake]], Gabe's best friend, on ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' and guest starred on many other TV shows as well.\n\nIn 2010, Albrizzi began acting in movies with appearances in ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'', ''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]'', and ''[[Treasure Buddies]]''. In 2011, he was originally cast in ''[[Ted (film)|Ted]]'' in the role of Robert, but he was unable to film because of scheduling conflicts with his work on the [[Disney XD]] pilot ''Pack of Wolves''. In the same year, he also got a role as the Kite Kid in ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''.\n\nIn 2016, Albrizzi co-starred in the science fiction action film ''[[Monster Trucks (film)|Monster Trucks]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/pitch-perfect-2-casting-chrissie-fit-monster-trucks-tucker-albrizzi-shohreh-aghdashloo/ |title=Chrissie Fit Cast In \u2018Pitch Perfect 2\u2032; Shohreh Aghdashloo To Narrate \u2018Alam High School\u2019; Tucker Albrizzi Joins \u2018Monster Trucks\u2019|accessdate=April 29, 2014|publisher=deadline.com |date=April 24, 2014}}</ref> In 2017, he starred in the feature film, ''Bully'', as the lead character Jimmy Mulligan.  Albrizzi also played the recurring role of Terry in 10 episodes of the YouTube series ''Foursome''. He also appeared as Randall Snyder in the first 4 episodes of the Netflix series ''[[American Vandal]]''.  Albrizzi appears in all 13 episodes of the first season of ''[[A.P. Bio]]'', as Colin McConnell. He plays Walter Dobbs in all 10 episodes of the first season of ''[[Mr. Iglesias]]'' on Netflix. \n\n===Voiceover work===\nAlbrizzi began [[voice acting]] with 2012's ''[[ParaNorman]]'', in the role of Neil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/livefrom/post/2011/07/paranorman-brings-together-an-outcast-kid-zombies-and-john-hughes/1|title='ParaNorman' brings together an outcast kid, zombies and John Hughes|work=usatoday.com|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref> He was also the voice of Budderball in ''[[Treasure Buddies]]'' (replacing [[Josh Flitter]] from the first ''[[Air Buddies]]'') and played the live-action role of Budderball's owner Bartleby in the [[Air Bud (series)|movies]].{{citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role \n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes \n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Sicko]]''\n|Himself\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''\n|Kite Kid\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]''\n|Skating Kid\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Spooky Buddies]]''\n|Bartleby\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[I Am Number Four (film)|I Am Number Four]]''\n|Tuck\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Treasure Buddies]]''\n|Budderball\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[ParaNorman]]''\n|Neil (voice)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Monster Trucks (film)|Monster Trucks]]''\n|Sam Geldon\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Bully''\n|Jimmy Mulligan\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[A.P. Bio]]'' (2018) Colin\n* ''[[American Vandal]]'' (2017) Randall Snyder\n* ''Shmagreggie Saves the World'' (2012) Lead role of Shmagreggie (pilot)\n* ''[[Lab Rats (US TV series)|Lab Rats]]'' (2012) Gordo (1 episode)\n* ''[[Disney XD]]'s Pack of Wolves'' (2011) Lead role of Darwin Oppenheimer\n* ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' (2010\u20132014) role of Jake (6 episodes)\n* ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (2009\u20132011) role of Tyler\n* ''[[Zeke and Luther]]'' (2011) role of Fish Belly (2 episodes)\n* ''[[Brothers & Sisters (2006 TV series)|Brothers & Sisters]]'' (2010) role of Kid playing Tybalt\n* ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'' (2010) role of Ricky\n* ''[[Mike & Molly]]'' (2010) role of Tucker\n* ''[[Childrens Hospital]]'' (2010) role of Kid\n* ''[[Dark Blue (TV series)|Dark Blue]]'' (2010) role of Marky\n* ''[[Tim and Eric Awesome Show, Great Job!]]'' (2010) role of iJammer\n* ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'' (2009) role of Son\n* ''[[The Jay Leno Show]]'' (2009) role of Flunker\n* ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]'' (2009) role of The Critics\n* ''Bless This Mess'' (2009) role of Michael\n* ''[[Mr. Iglesias]]'' (2019) role of Walter\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* [[32nd Young Artist Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html|title=32nd Annual Young Artist Awards \u2013 Nominations / Special Awards|work=youngartistawards.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>\n** Best Guest Star Performance in a TV Series \u2013 ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' (Won)\n** Best Recurring Performance in a TV Series \u2013 ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (Nominated)\n* [[33rd Young Artist Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms33.html|title=33rd Annual Young Artist Awards \u2013 Nominations / Special Awards|work=youngartistawards.org|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>\n** Best Performance in a TV Series \u2013 Guest Starring Young Actor Ten and Under \u2013 ''[[Big Time Rush]]'' (Nominated)\n** Best Performance in a DVD Film \u2013 Young Ensemble Cast \u2013 ''[[Spooky Buddies]]'' (Won)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.tuckeralbrizzi.com/ Official website]\n* {{IMDb name|3235380}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Albrizzi, Tucker}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:People from Palm Harbor, Florida]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Florida]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n", "name_user": "Eriru", "