ond Album on Cash Money, Feature Lil Wayne|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=May 22, 2013}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Country\n!Release date\n!format\n|-\n|Worldwide\n|{{start date|2006|6|5}}\n|[[Music download|Digital download]]\n|-\n|United States\n|{{start date|2006|6|6}}\n|[[American Top 40|Top 40]]/[[Contemporary hit radio|Mainstream radio]]\n|-\n|Australia\n|{{start date|2006|7|8}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Digital download\n|-\n|United Kingdom\n|{{start date|2006|7|31}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.vevo.com/watch/paris-hilton/Stars-Are-Blind-New-Version-(Video)/USWBV0600402 Music video on VEVO]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|paris-hilton|stars-are-blind}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Paris Hilton}}\n\n[[Category:2006 songs]]\n[[Category:2006 debut singles]]\n[[Category:Paris Hilton songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Chris Applebaum]]\n[[Category:American reggae songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sheppard Solomon]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Fernando Garibay]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Luny Tunes]]\n[[Category:Songs involved in plagiarism controversies]]\n[[Category:Black-and-white music videos]]\n", "name_user": "107.213.2.58", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(added content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stars_Are_Blind"}
{"title_page": "PrettyMuch", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = PrettyMuch\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = PrettyMuch - FOMO Tour 2019.png\n| image_size       = 300px\n| caption          = PrettyMuch in 2019.\n| alias            = \n| origin           = <!-- Do not add the hometowns of the group members here; this space is to document the city in which the group was formed --> [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"MTV\" />\n}}\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = [[French Montana]], [[Rich the Kid]], [[Lil Tjay]], [[CNCO]], [[NCT Dream]], [[Lu\u00edsa Sonza]], [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]]\n| website          = {{URL|prettymuch.com/}}\n| current_members  = * Brandon Arreaga\n* Edwin Honoret\n* Austin Porter\n* Nick Mara\n* Zion Kuwonu\n}}\n\n'''PrettyMuch''', stylized as '''PRETTYMUCH''', is an American-Canadian [[Pop music|pop]] [[boy band]] based in Los Angeles, California. The group consists of Brandon Arreaga, Edwin Honoret, Austin Porter, Nick Mara, and Zion Kuwonu. The boy band was formed by [[Simon Cowell]] in 2016.\nIn April of 2020, #PRETTYMUCHISOVERPARTY trended worldwide due to the band being accused of incest. This soon resulted in the groups disband\n\n==Career==\n===2016&ndash;2017: Formation and early career===\nThe members of PrettyMuch were pursuing solo careers until [[Syco Music]] founder Simon Cowell and former label president Sonny Takhar merged them into a group.<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/prettymuch-simon-cowell-boy-band-teen-choice-1202509967/|title=PrettyMuch, Simon Cowell\u2019s Latest Boy Band Discovery, Poised to Pop|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Michele Amabile|last=Angermiller |date=July 28, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7940930/prettymuch-why-dont-we-cnco-boy-bands-interview|title=Meet the Next Wave of Boy Bands: PRETTYMUCH, Why Don't We and CNCO|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Steven J.|last=Horowitz|date=August 24, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> Since 2016, the members of PrettyMuch have been based in [[Los Angeles]] where they have shared a home since March 18, 2016, in which they have worked on their dancing skills in addition to recording their debut EP.<ref name=\"Variety\" /><ref name=\"NYDailyNews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/new-simon-cowell-boy-band-pretty-latest-article-1.3502651|title=New Simon Cowell boy band is Prettymuch the latest thing|website=[[New York Daily News]]|first=Ray|last=Monell|date=September 17, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, PrettyMuch gained attention on social media with their cover songs and dancing videos, including a rendition of [[Charlie Puth]]'s \"[[Attention (Charlie Puth song)|Attention]]\" and choreography tributes to [[Michael Jackson]] and [[Bruno Mars]].<ref name=\"MTV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3036230/prettymuch-would-you-mind-video/|title=PRETTYMUCH's Sunny 'Would You Mind' Video Looks Like It's From 1997|website=[[MTV]]|first=Patrick|last=Hosken|date=September 15, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=http://people.com/music/simon-cowell-new-boy-band-pretty-much/|title=Meet Simon Cowell's New Boy Band,PRETTYMUCH (Spoiler: They're Adorable and They Can Really Dance)|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|first=Aurelie|last=Corinthios|date=May 13, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/09/19/prettymuch-would-you-mind-music-video/|title=Simon Cowell's boy band PRETTYMUCH drops \u2018Would You Mind' music video \u2014 watch now|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Thatiana|last=Diaz|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> PrettyMuch's debut single, \"Would You Mind\", written by Savan Kotecha and Jacob Kasher, was released in July 2017.<ref name=\"EW\" /><ref name=\"Idolator\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7665887/prettymuch-debut-single-would-you-mind-snippet|title=Meet Your New Favorite Boy Band: PRETTYMUCH Teases \"Would You Mind\" |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|first=Mike|last=Wass|date=July 7, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> A month later, the group performed the song at the [[2017 Teen Choice Awards]] and sang an [[a cappella]] version on the red carpet at the [[2017 MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref name=\"NYDailyNews\" /><ref name=\"MTV\" /> A music video for the song was then released in September. Directed by [[Emil Nava]], it depicts the members dancing and jumping over each other in empty alleyways, along with scenes from a road trip the group had taken.<ref name=\"Billboard1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7965767/prettymuch-would-you-mind-video|title=PRETTYMUCH Drops 'Would You Mind' Video|website=Billboard.com|first=Megan|last=Armstrong|date=September 15, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"MTV1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3036757/prettymuch-emil-nava-would-you-mind-behind-the-scenes/|title=PRETTYMUCH Director Breaks Down The Influences Behind 'Would You Mind' Video |website=MTV|first=Patrick|last=Hosken|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> The clip was inspired by boy band videos of the late 1990s and early 2000s, such as [[Backstreet Boys]]' \"[[We've Got It Goin' On]]\" and [[NSYNC]]'s \"[[I Want You Back (NSYNC song)|I Want You Back]]\".<ref name=\"MTV1\" /> The single peaked in the top 40 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Mainstream Top 40]] charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/prettymuch/chart-history|title=PRETTYMUCH|website=Billboard.com}}</ref>\n\nPrettyMuch performed \"Would You Mind\" on MTV's ''[[Total Request Live]]'' in October 2017 and released their second single, \"Teacher\".<ref name=\"MTV2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3040047/prettymuch-teacher-women-empowerment/|title=PRETTYMUCH's New Single Is All About 'Women Empowerment, 100 Percent'|website=MTV|first=Madeline|last=Roth|date=October 5, 2017|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}</ref> This single and its video clip have been accused of being very similar to those of [[Dead Obies]]' \"Where They @\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journaldemontreal.com/2017/10/13/video-dead-obies-plagie-par-un-boys-band-americain|title=[VID\u00c9O] Dead Obies plagi\u00e9 par un boys band am\u00e9ricain?|last=Plante|first=St\u00e9phane|work=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|access-date=2018-04-21|language=fr-CA}}</ref> On October 27, 2017, they released their single, \"Open Arms\". In November 2017, they confirmed via Twitter that they would perform during the final of [[The X Factor (UK series 14)|Series 14]] of ''[[The X Factor (UK TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in the [[United Kingdom]], performing their single, \"No More\".<ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PRETTYMUCH/status/935948105064878080|title='Twitter'|website=Twitter|date=November 29, 2017|accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref> PrettyMuch had their own tour called PRETTYMUCH EVERYWHERE Tour across the United States. The group performed on Good Morning America on January 15. PrettyMuch performed their singles \"Open Arms\" and \"No More\" on MTV's ''[[Total Request Live]] ''on January 17.\n\n===2018&ndash;present: ''PrettyMuch an EP'', ''Phases'', and ''INTL:EP''===\nThey released their debut EP, ''PrettyMuch an EP'' on April 19, 2018, including their single \"10,000 Hours\". On June 21, 2018, they released their summer single \"Summer On You\", written by [[Ed Sheeran]] and produced by [[Steve Mac]].<ref name=\"Billboard2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8462126/prettymuch-summer-on-you|title=PRETTYMUCH Drops Sunny Ed Sheeran-Penned Single 'Summer on You': Listen|website=Billboard.com|first=Sofia|last=Mele|date=June 21, 2018|accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref> They also performed it on the Late Late Show with [[James Corden]]. On August 20, 2018, the group performed at the [[MTV Video Music Awards|2018 MTV Video Music Awards]] on the Push Artist Stage.<ref name=\"MTV3\">{{cite web|url= http://www.mtv.com/vma/performers|title=2018 VMA Performers|website=MTV|date=August 17, 2018|accessdate=August 20, 2018}}</ref> The single peaked in the top 50 on [[Pop radio]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Brian |last=Cantor |title=Songs By Marshmello & Bastille, Panic! At The Disco, PRETTYMUCH Join Pop Radio\u2019s Top 50 |website=Headline Planet |url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2018/08/26/songs-marshmello-bastille-panic-disco-prettymuch-join-pop-radios-top-50/ |access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> On September 28, 2018, they released their single \"Solita\" featuring [[Rich the Kid]].<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/prettymuch-new-song-solita-rich-the-kid-730179/|title=Hear PrettyMuch's Feisty New Song 'Solita'|website=Rolling Stone|first=Brittany|last=Spanos|date=September 28, 2018|accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey released their song \"Real Friends\" on October 17, 2018, to promote their fall tour, the Funktion Tour. Not long after ending their tour, they released a new song \"Jello\" on December 14, 2018, accompanied by an official video. In the start of 2019, \"BLiND\" was released on January 25. This was the band's first single since \"Would You Mind\" that was not performed live prior to the studio version being released. Their second single of 2019, \"Phases\", was released on April 26. On May 17, PrettyMuch announced their second EP would come out a week later. On May 20, the band released \"Gone 2 Long\", a previously mentioned song that was written and produced completely by Brandon Arreaga and would be featured on their new EP. The group's second EP, the ''Phases - EP'', was released on May 24, 2019. The EP consists of six songs: two already released songs (\"Phases\" and \"Gone 2 Long\"), and four new songs called \"Eyes Off You\", \"Temporary Heart\", \"4U\" and \"One Shot\".\n\nOn July 11, PrettyMuch kicked off their [[The FOMO Tour|FOMO Tour]] with opening act [[Kenzie Ziegler]] in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]]. A week later, on July 19, the band released \"Lying\", a collaboration with [[Lil Tjay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/prettymuch-lying-lil-tjay-new-video-fomo-tour-861070/|title=Watch PrettyMuch, Lil Tjay\u2019s Graffiti-Covered \u2018Lying\u2019 Video|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|last2=Spanos|first2=Brittany|date=2019-07-19|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref> After being on the FOMO tour setlist, \"Rock Witchu\" was released as an official audio.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2WzrtZh8apc] {{dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref> This track was previously released as a behind the scenes, studio version on YouTube titled \"Making Music In Our Garage Studio\" on April 16,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BMeeHuztano] {{dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref> but after the support for the track in concert, it was released officially August 16. This is the second PrettyMuch track that was produced by [[Brandon Arreaga]].\n\nIn February 2019 during an interview with Hollywire, Edwin Honoret hinted at an upcoming collaboration, stating that it might be \"the first time two boy bands have been on a song together.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/video/prettymuch-upcoming-collab/|title=Edwin Honoret Teases PRETTYMUCH\u2019s Upcoming Boyband Collaboration {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> In April 2019, it was confirmed that PrettyMuch would be collaborating on a song with Latin-American boy band [[CNCO]] with both boy bands giving confirmation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/etnow/status/1121576119755403264?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1121576119755403264&ref_url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/18515/cnco-prettymuch-ultimate-boyband-collab|title=The boys of @CNCOmusic dropped serious details on their upcoming collab with @PRETTYMUCH at the Latin #Billboards2019 and we cannot wait for this !!!!pic.twitter.com/jAO701NiOq|last=Tonight|first=Entertainment|date=2019-04-25|website=@etnow|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BwsNyLABOuf/|title=\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25 on Instagram: \"\u2022 What do you guys think? One of the greatest boyband collabs to come? \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffd \u2022 @prettymuch @cncomusic @therealnickmara @zionkuwonu\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> On October 19, 2019, both PrettyMuch and CNCO confirmed on their social media pages that their song, \"Me Necesita\", would be released on October 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3xowWcgjme/|title=PRETTYMUCH on Instagram: \"the time has FINALLY come! our collaboration with @cncomusic 'Me Necesita' is coming on 10.23.19 and it\u2019s going to be EPIC! #MeNecesita\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3xpzDah7oz/|title=CNCO on Instagram: \"#MeNecesita x @prettymuch COMING 10/23 \ud83d\udd25 Let\u2019s get it!!\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> On November 22, PrettyMuch released ''INTL:EP'', which features \"Me Necesita\" alongside three other songs, with guest vocals from [[Lu\u00edsa Sonza]], [[NCT Dream]], and [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |title=PrettyMuch Discuss Guest-Filled 'Intl:EP,' Ambitious 2020 Plans |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/prettymuch-interview-intl-ep-cnco-nct-dream-911886/ |access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> On March 10, 2020, PrettyMuch was announced as an opening act for select US dates of [[Camila Cabello]]'s [[The Romance Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9332170/camila-cabello-announces-prettymuch-trevor-daniel-ant-saunders-romance-tour-guests|title=Camila Cabello Announces Romance Tour Opening Acts|date=March 10, 2020|website=Billboard.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = PrettyMuch\n| Image        =\n| Alt          =\n| Caption      =\n| Studio       =\n| EP           = 3\n| Compilation  =\n| Video        =\n| Music videos = 15\n| Singles      = 18\n}}\nPrettyMuch have released three [[extended plays]], eighteen [[single (music)|singles]], and fifteen [[music videos]].\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17em;\"| Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''PrettyMuch an EP''\n|\n* Release date: April 19, 2018\n* Label: [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* Format: [[Music download|Digital download]], [[streaming media|streaming]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Phases - EP''\n|\n* Release date: May 24, 2019\n* Label: Syco\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''INTL:EP''\n|\n* Release date: November 22, 2019\n* Label: Syco\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Mainstream Top 40|US Pop]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/prettymuch/chart-history/pop-songs|title=Billboard Pop Songs|publisher=[[Billboard (chart)]]|date=October 7, 2017|accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ<br>Hot]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4575|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=December 24, 2018|accessdate=December 21, 2018}}\n* \"Lying\": {{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4727|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=July 29, 2019|accessdate=July 27, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51938/prettymuch/|title=PrettyMuch {{!}} full Official Chart history|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=December 16, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Would You Mind\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2017\n| 40 || \u2014 || 100\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Teacher\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Open Arms\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"No More\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[French Montana]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || 77\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hello\"\n| rowspan=\"8\"| 2018\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''PrettyMuch an EP''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"10,000 Hours\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Healthy\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"On My Way\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Summer On You\"\n| 49 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"5\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Solita\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Rich the Kid]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Real Friends\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Jello\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/jello-single/1445718198|title=Jello \u2013 Single by PRETTYMUCH on iTunes|website=iTunes Store|accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || 34 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Blind\"\n| rowspan=\"7\"| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Phases\"\n| \u2014 || 26 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Phases EP''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Gone 2 Long\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Lying\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Lil Tjay]])}}<ref>{{cite tweet|user=PRETTYMUCH|number=1148996960025792513|title=NEW SINGLE. LYING. FT @liltjay \ud83d\ude08 07/19|date=July 10, 2019|website=Twitter.com|accessdate=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || 19 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Rock Witchu\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/rock-witchu-single/1476053768|title=Rock Witchu \u2013 Single by PrettyMuch|website=Apple Music|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Me Necesita\"<br />{{small|(with [[CNCO]])}}<ref name=prettymuch>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8540076/prettymuch-cnco-me-necesita-video|title=Watch Prettymuch & CNCO Team Up For an Epic Boy Band Battle in 'Me Necesita' Video|website=Billboard.com|date=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''INTL:EP''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Up to You\"<br />{{small|(with [[NCT Dream]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n* \"Would You Mind\" (2017)\n* \"Teacher\" (2017)\n* \"Open Arms\" (2017)\n* \"No More\" (2017) with French Montana\n* \"10,000 Hours\" (2018)\n* \"Hello\" (2018)\n* \"Summer On You\" (2018)\n* \"Jello\" (2018)\n* \"Blind\" (2019)\n* \"Phases\" (2019)\n* \"Gone 2 Long (Choir Version)\" (2019)\n* \"Lying\" (2019) with Lil Tjay\n* \"Me Necesita\" (2019) with CNCO\n* \"The Weekend\" (2019) with Lu\u00edsa Sonza\n* \"Love\" (2019) with I\u00f1igo Pascual\n\n== Members ==\n=== Brandon Arreaga ===\nBrandon Michael Lee Arreaga (born December 14, 1999) grew up in Corinth, Texas. He began doing acting and modeling jobs at around eleven years old, and used money earned from the jobs to get equipment for a home studio.<ref>[https://schonmagazine.com/interview-prettymuch/ \"interview<nowiki> |</nowiki> prettymuch\"], ''Sch\u00f6n!''. Retrieved 2019-11-04.</ref> Arreaga would rent the studio out to other local musicians.<ref name=\"Zach Sang Show 2017\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l7gRuTme74w PRETTYMUCH talks Would You Mind, One Direction and French Montana], ''Zach Sang Show''.</ref> He was the last member to join the group, as he did not initially get involved because his parents thought the scouting was fake.<ref name=\"Idolator 2017\">[https://www.idolator.com/7666497/prettymuch-interview-would-you-mind \"PRETTYMUCH On Boy Band Life & Debut Single \u201cWould You Mind\u201d: Interview\"], ''Idolator''. Retrieved 2019-11-04.</ref> As of 2019, Arreaga has been dating [[Maggie Lindemann]], another singer from Texas.<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/B0KmXMtnO4L/ \u2606 BRANDON ARREAGA \u2606 on Instagram: \"u are actually the most beautiful thing I think I\u2019ve ever seen in my life no cap...\"]. ''Instagram''. Retrieved 2019-11-04.</ref>\n\n=== Edwin Honoret ===\nEdwin Joel Honoret (born February 12, 1999) is from [[The Bronx]], New York.<ref name=\"Zach Sang Show 2017\" /> \n\n=== Nick Mara ===\nNicholas Carter Mara (born November 8, 1997) was born in [[New York City|New York]], but grew up in [[Englishtown, New Jersey|Englishtown]], New Jersey. He began dancing at around nine years old, and was formerly in the dance crew ICONic Boyz, which was featured in the sixth season of [[America's Best Dance Crew (season 6)|America's Best Dance Crew]]. Mara describes his musical interest as \"Bad Boy-era type music\", being inspired by artists such as [[Notorious B.I.G]].<ref name=\"Teen Vogue 2017\">[https://www.teenvogue.com/story/prettymuch-interview-musical-influences-being-in-a-boy-band Prettymuch Gets Real About Musical Influences and Being in a Boy Band], ''Teen Vogue''. Retrieved 2019-11-04.</ref>\n\n=== Austin Porter ===\nAustin Dale Porter (born August 14, 1997) grew up in [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte]], North Carolina. Prior to the audition, Porter had a solo career, having made an unreleased rap EP.<ref name=\"Zach Sang Show 2017\" /> He is inspired by a variety of different genres including lo-fi hip-hop and jazz. He has listed [[Elton John]], [[James Taylor]], [[Chicago (band)|Chicago]] and [[The Beatles]] as some of his musical influences.<ref>[http://www.digitaljournal.com/entertainment/music/prettymuch-talks-new-single-summer-on-you-ed-sheeran-beyonce/article/526766 PRETTYMUCH talks new single 'Summer on You,' Ed Sheeran, Beyonce], ''Digital Journal''.</ref>\n\n=== Zion Kuwonu ===\nCaleb Zion Kuwonu (born June 29, 1999) is from [[Ottawa]], Canada. He was inspired to become a singer after watching [[Justin Bieber: Never Say Never]], and lists [[Justin Bieber]] as one of his musical inspirations, among other artists such as [[PartyNextDoor]], [[One Direction]], and [[Michael Jackson]].<ref name=\"Idolator 2017\" /><ref name=\"Teen Vogue 2017\" /> Kuwonu was noticed by [[Sony Music]] after he began posting song covers on [[Vine (service)|Vine]] in order to gain popularity at school. He has noted that he only had around 150 followers at the time.<ref name=\"Zach Sang Show 2017\" />\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Nominated\n! scope=\"col\" | Nominated\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2018\n|[[2018 iHeartRadio Music Awards|iHeart Radio Music Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 iHeartRadio Music Awards: See The Full List Of Nominees & Winners|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-03-10-2018-iheartradio-music-awards-see-the-full-list-of-nominees-winners/|work=[[iHeartRadio]]|date=2018-03-10|accessdate=2018-07-16}}</ref>\n|Best Boyband\n| rowspan=\"6\" |PRETTYMUCH\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|[[2018 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-vmas-winners-see-complete-list-1135082/item/best-pop-2018-vma-noms-1127265 |title=2018 VMAs Winners: See the Complete List |magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=July 16, 2018}}</ref>\n|Push Artist of the Year\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2018 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8478247/2018-mtv-ema-camila-cabello-ariana-grande-post-malone-nominees|title=Camila Cabello, Ariana Grande, Post Malone Lead 2018 MTV EMA Nominees|date=October 4, 2018|website=Billboard.com}}</ref>\n|Best Push\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Best Group\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2019\n|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list-updating-live-1229486/item/choice-action-movie-1229382 \"Teen Choice Awards: Full List of Winners\"], ''The Hollywood Reporter'', accessed August 16, 2019</ref>\n|Choice Music Group\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|[[2019 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8527728/2019-vmas-pre-show-performers-exclusive 2019 VMAs Reveal Three New Fan-Voted Categories, Pre-Show Performers], August 19, 2019</ref>\n|Best Group\n|{{nominated}}\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n'''Headlining'''\n* [[PRETTYMUCH EVERYWHERE Tour]] (2018)\n* [[FUNKTION Tour]] (2018)\n* [[FOMO Tour]] (2019)\n\n'''Opening act'''\n* Jack & Jack Tour (2017)\n* [[Roxy Tour]] (2018)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.prettymuch.com/}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2016 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:American boy bands]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2016]]\n[[Category:Syco Music artists]]\n[[Category:Vocal quintets]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = PrettyMuch\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = PrettyMuch - FOMO Tour 2019.png\n| image_size       = 300px\n| caption          = PrettyMuch in 2019.\n| alias            = \n| origin           = <!-- Do not add the hometowns of the group members here; this space is to document the city in which the group was formed --> [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"MTV\" />\n}}\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = [[French Montana]], [[Rich the Kid]], [[Lil Tjay]], [[CNCO]], [[NCT Dream]], [[Lu\u00edsa Sonza]], [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]]\n| website          = {{URL|prettymuch.com/}}\n| current_members  = * Brandon Arreaga\n* Edwin Honoret\n* Austin Porter\n* Nick Mara\n* Zion Kuwonu\n}}\n\n'''PrettyMuch''', stylized as '''PRETTYMUCH''', is an American-Canadian [[Pop music|pop]] [[boy band]] based in Los Angeles, California. The group consists of Brandon Arreaga, Edwin Honoret, Austin Porter, Nick Mara, and Zion Kuwonu. The boy band was formed by [[Simon Cowell]] in 2016.\n\n==Career==\n===2016&ndash;2017: Formation and early career===\nThe members of PrettyMuch were pursuing solo careers until [[Syco Music]] founder Simon Cowell and former label president Sonny Takhar merged them into a group.<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/prettymuch-simon-cowell-boy-band-teen-choice-1202509967/|title=PrettyMuch, Simon Cowell\u2019s Latest Boy Band Discovery, Poised to Pop|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Michele Amabile|last=Angermiller |date=July 28, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7940930/prettymuch-why-dont-we-cnco-boy-bands-interview|title=Meet the Next Wave of Boy Bands: PRETTYMUCH, Why Don't We and CNCO|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Steven J.|last=Horowitz|date=August 24, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> Since 2016, the members of PrettyMuch have been based in [[Los Angeles]] where they have shared a home since March 18, 2016, in which they have worked on their dancing skills in addition to recording their debut EP.<ref name=\"Variety\" /><ref name=\"NYDailyNews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/new-simon-cowell-boy-band-pretty-latest-article-1.3502651|title=New Simon Cowell boy band is Prettymuch the latest thing|website=[[New York Daily News]]|first=Ray|last=Monell|date=September 17, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, PrettyMuch gained attention on social media with their cover songs and dancing videos, including a rendition of [[Charlie Puth]]'s \"[[Attention (Charlie Puth song)|Attention]]\" and choreography tributes to [[Michael Jackson]] and [[Bruno Mars]].<ref name=\"MTV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3036230/prettymuch-would-you-mind-video/|title=PRETTYMUCH's Sunny 'Would You Mind' Video Looks Like It's From 1997|website=[[MTV]]|first=Patrick|last=Hosken|date=September 15, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=http://people.com/music/simon-cowell-new-boy-band-pretty-much/|title=Meet Simon Cowell's New Boy Band,PRETTYMUCH (Spoiler: They're Adorable and They Can Really Dance)|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|first=Aurelie|last=Corinthios|date=May 13, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/09/19/prettymuch-would-you-mind-music-video/|title=Simon Cowell's boy band PRETTYMUCH drops \u2018Would You Mind' music video \u2014 watch now|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Thatiana|last=Diaz|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> PrettyMuch's debut single, \"Would You Mind\", written by Savan Kotecha and Jacob Kasher, was released in July 2017.<ref name=\"EW\" /><ref name=\"Idolator\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7665887/prettymuch-debut-single-would-you-mind-snippet|title=Meet Your New Favorite Boy Band: PRETTYMUCH Teases \"Would You Mind\" |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|first=Mike|last=Wass|date=July 7, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> A month later, the group performed the song at the [[2017 Teen Choice Awards]] and sang an [[a cappella]] version on the red carpet at the [[2017 MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref name=\"NYDailyNews\" /><ref name=\"MTV\" /> A music video for the song was then released in September. Directed by [[Emil Nava]], it depicts the members dancing and jumping over each other in empty alleyways, along with scenes from a road trip the group had taken.<ref name=\"Billboard1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7965767/prettymuch-would-you-mind-video|title=PRETTYMUCH Drops 'Would You Mind' Video|website=Billboard.com|first=Megan|last=Armstrong|date=September 15, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"MTV1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3036757/prettymuch-emil-nava-would-you-mind-behind-the-scenes/|title=PRETTYMUCH Director Breaks Down The Influences Behind 'Would You Mind' Video |website=MTV|first=Patrick|last=Hosken|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> The clip was inspired by boy band videos of the late 1990s and early 2000s, such as [[Backstreet Boys]]' \"[[We've Got It Goin' On]]\" and [[NSYNC]]'s \"[[I Want You Back (NSYNC song)|I Want You Back]]\".<ref name=\"MTV1\" /> The single peaked in the top 40 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Mainstream Top 40]] charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/prettymuch/chart-history|title=PRETTYMUCH|website=Billboard.com}}</ref>\n\nPrettyMuch performed \"Would You Mind\" on MTV's ''[[Total Request Live]]'' in October 2017 and released their second single, \"Teacher\".<ref name=\"MTV2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3040047/prettymuch-teacher-women-empowerment/|title=PRETTYMUCH's New Single Is All About 'Women Empowerment, 100 Percent'|website=MTV|first=Madeline|last=Roth|date=October 5, 2017|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}</ref> This single and its video clip have been accused of being very similar to those of [[Dead Obies]]' \"Where They @\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journaldemontreal.com/2017/10/13/video-dead-obies-plagie-par-un-boys-band-americain|title=[VID\u00c9O] Dead Obies plagi\u00e9 par un boys band am\u00e9ricain?|last=Plante|first=St\u00e9phane|work=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|access-date=2018-04-21|language=fr-CA}}</ref> On October 27, 2017, they released their single, \"Open Arms\". In November 2017, they confirmed via Twitter that they would perform during the final of [[The X Factor (UK series 14)|Series 14]] of ''[[The X Factor (UK TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in the [[United Kingdom]], performing their single, \"No More\".<ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PRETTYMUCH/status/935948105064878080|title='Twitter'|website=Twitter|date=November 29, 2017|accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref> PrettyMuch had their own tour called PRETTYMUCH EVERYWHERE Tour across the United States. The group performed on Good Morning America on January 15. PrettyMuch performed their singles \"Open Arms\" and \"No More\" on MTV's ''[[Total Request Live]] ''on January 17.\n\n===2018&ndash;present: ''PrettyMuch an EP'', ''Phases'', and ''INTL:EP''===\nThey released their debut EP, ''PrettyMuch an EP'' on April 19, 2018, including their single \"10,000 Hours\". On June 21, 2018, they released their summer single \"Summer On You\", written by [[Ed Sheeran]] and produced by [[Steve Mac]].<ref name=\"Billboard2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8462126/prettymuch-summer-on-you|title=PRETTYMUCH Drops Sunny Ed Sheeran-Penned Single 'Summer on You': Listen|website=Billboard.com|first=Sofia|last=Mele|date=June 21, 2018|accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref> They also performed it on the Late Late Show with [[James Corden]]. On August 20, 2018, the group performed at the [[MTV Video Music Awards|2018 MTV Video Music Awards]] on the Push Artist Stage.<ref name=\"MTV3\">{{cite web|url= http://www.mtv.com/vma/performers|title=2018 VMA Performers|website=MTV|date=August 17, 2018|accessdate=August 20, 2018}}</ref> The single peaked in the top 50 on [[Pop radio]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Brian |last=Cantor |title=Songs By Marshmello & Bastille, Panic! At The Disco, PRETTYMUCH Join Pop Radio\u2019s Top 50 |website=Headline Planet |url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2018/08/26/songs-marshmello-bastille-panic-disco-prettymuch-join-pop-radios-top-50/ |access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> On September 28, 2018, they released their single \"Solita\" featuring [[Rich the Kid]].<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/prettymuch-new-song-solita-rich-the-kid-730179/|title=Hear PrettyMuch's Feisty New Song 'Solita'|website=Rolling Stone|first=Brittany|last=Spanos|date=September 28, 2018|accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey released their song \"Real Friends\" on October 17, 2018, to promote their fall tour, the Funktion Tour. Not long after ending their tour, they released a new song \"Jello\" on December 14, 2018, accompanied by an official video. In the start of 2019, \"BLiND\" was released on January 25. This was the band's first single since \"Would You Mind\" that was not performed live prior to the studio version being released. Their second single of 2019, \"Phases\", was released on April 26. On May 17, PrettyMuch announced their second EP would come out a week later. On May 20, the band released \"Gone 2 Long\", a previously mentioned song that was written and produced completely by Brandon Arreaga and would be featured on their new EP. The group's second EP, the ''Phases - EP'', was released on May 24, 2019. The EP consists of six songs: two already released songs (\"Phases\" and \"Gone 2 Long\"), and four new songs called \"Eyes Off You\", \"Temporary Heart\", \"4U\" and \"One Shot\".\n\nOn July 11, PrettyMuch kicked off their [[The FOMO Tour|FOMO Tour]] with opening act [[Kenzie Ziegler]] in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]]. A week later, on July 19, the band released \"Lying\", a collaboration with [[Lil Tjay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/prettymuch-lying-lil-tjay-new-video-fomo-tour-861070/|title=Watch PrettyMuch, Lil Tjay\u2019s Graffiti-Covered \u2018Lying\u2019 Video|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|last2=Spanos|first2=Brittany|date=2019-07-19|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref> After being on the FOMO tour setlist, \"Rock Witchu\" was released as an official audio.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2WzrtZh8apc] {{dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref> This track was previously released as a behind the scenes, studio version on YouTube titled \"Making Music In Our Garage Studio\" on April 16,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BMeeHuztano] {{dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref> but after the support for the track in concert, it was released officially August 16. This is the second PrettyMuch track that was produced by [[Brandon Arreaga]].\n\nIn February 2019 during an interview with Hollywire, Edwin Honoret hinted at an upcoming collaboration, stating that it might be \"the first time two boy bands have been on a song together.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/video/prettymuch-upcoming-collab/|title=Edwin Honoret Teases PRETTYMUCH\u2019s Upcoming Boyband Collaboration {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> In April 2019, it was confirmed that PrettyMuch would be collaborating on a song with Latin-American boy band [[CNCO]] with both boy bands giving confirmation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/etnow/status/1121576119755403264?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1121576119755403264&ref_url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/18515/cnco-prettymuch-ultimate-boyband-collab|title=The boys of @CNCOmusic dropped serious details on their upcoming collab with @PRETTYMUCH at the Latin #Billboards2019 and we cannot wait for this !!!!pic.twitter.com/jAO701NiOq|last=Tonight|first=Entertainment|date=2019-04-25|website=@etnow|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BwsNyLABOuf/|title=\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25 on Instagram: \"\u2022 What do you guys think? One of the greatest boyband collabs to come? \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffd \u2022 @prettymuch @cncomusic @therealnickmara @zionkuwonu\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> On October 19, 2019, both PrettyMuch and CNCO confirmed on their social media pages that their song, \"Me Necesita\", would be released on October 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3xowWcgjme/|title=PRETTYMUCH on Instagram: \"the time has FINALLY come! our collaboration with @cncomusic 'Me Necesita' is coming on 10.23.19 and it\u2019s going to be EPIC! #MeNecesita\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3xpzDah7oz/|title=CNCO on Instagram: \"#MeNecesita x @prettymuch COMING 10/23 \ud83d\udd25 Let\u2019s get it!!\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-10-19}}</ref> On November 22, PrettyMuch released ''INTL:EP'', which features \"Me Necesita\" alongside three other songs, with guest vocals from [[Lu\u00edsa Sonza]], [[NCT Dream]], and [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |title=PrettyMuch Discuss Guest-Filled 'Intl:EP,' Ambitious 2020 Plans |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/prettymuch-interview-intl-ep-cnco-nct-dream-911886/ |access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> On March 10, 2020, PrettyMuch was announced as an opening act for select US dates of [[Camila Cabello]]'s [[The Romance Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9332170/camila-cabello-announces-prettymuch-trevor-daniel-ant-saunders-romance-tour-guests|title=Camila Cabello Announces Romance Tour Opening Acts|date=March 10, 2020|website=Billboard.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = PrettyMuch\n| Image        =\n| Alt          =\n| Caption      =\n| Studio       =\n| EP           = 3\n| Compilation  =\n| Video        =\n| Music videos = 15\n| Singles      = 18\n}}\nPrettyMuch have released three [[extended plays]], eighteen [[single (music)|singles]], and fifteen [[music videos]].\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17em;\"| Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''PrettyMuch an EP''\n|\n* Release date: April 19, 2018\n* Label: [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* Format: [[Music download|Digital download]], [[streaming media|streaming]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Phases - EP''\n|\n* Release date: May 24, 2019\n* Label: Syco\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''INTL:EP''\n|\n* Release date: November 22, 2019\n* Label: Syco\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Mainstream Top 40|US Pop]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/prettymuch/chart-history/pop-songs|title=Billboard Pop Songs|publisher=[[Billboard (chart)]]|date=October 7, 2017|accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ<br>Hot]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4575|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=December 24, 2018|accessdate=December 21, 2018}}\n* \"Lying\": {{cite web|url=h